Both required outputs are written and validated against the schema.

**transcript.json** — 18 iterations, 61 hypotheses, 61 analyses, validated against `transcript_schema.json`. Top-level fields set as required (`dataset_id=ds001_nsclc`, `model_id=claude-opus-4-7`, `harness_id=claude-code@nsclc-named-1`, `max_iterations=25`).

**analysis_summary.txt** — narrative synthesis covering supported and refuted hypotheses.

Headline findings:
- Pembrolizumab benefit is strongly conditional on biomarkers: pembro × PD-L1 TPS interaction β=+0.59 (p=1.6e-7); pembro × TMB-high β=+0.18 (p=4e-4); pembro × STK11 β=−0.21 (p=1.8e-3, attenuates benefit).
- Joint PD-L1 ≥50% + TMB-high yields +13.9pp absolute ORR gain on pembrolizumab (p=2e-20).
- Standard prognostics (ECOG, stage IV, brain mets, albumin, CRP, weight loss) all significant in expected directions, robust in multivariable model.
- Pembro benefit is concentrated in ever-smokers; female sex amplifies it (interaction p=2.4e-3).
- **Striking null:** the targeted-therapy axes (osimertinib×EGFR, sotorasib×KRAS-G12C, olaparib×BRCA2) show no biomarker-matched benefit. SNP panel, most comorbidities, insurance, rural residence, and most other genomic alterations are uninformative.
